snippet.textDisplay: Come on Joe, you're smarter than that. I for one is sick and tired of people trying to downplay this pandemic and saying its only bad for older or people or people with underlying factors. Are you kidding me? The medical system will be overwhelmed. So no matter what your age, health and meat diet, you will die if you get appendicitis, a heart attack, a stroke, a compound fracture, a severe laceration or any other medical emergency for which you will not get treated. The world as we no it is over. Whatever it becomes will be very different. It sounds crass, but its probably the best thing that could happen to our world. The economic system is over, a lot of excesses are over, and a lot of the pettiness, racism, etc will become trivial. Either you shut everything down or you become another Italy. Its as simple as that. I realize many entrepreneurs worked hard for their businesses, they probably won't survive, but they won't have any customers even if they make it through. Sad but true. There will be no real recovery until a vaccine is developed and distributed. No one will work for a minimum wage to make socks while risking their lives. You may think you're in a privileged situation right now...but look ahead 12 to 18 months and tell me how it feels.

snippet.textDisplay:
Im one of those “cant afford a $300-400 expense or Im screwed for months people” I do carpentry work, have a degree in architectural drafting and work at a liquor store! I have the answer to who we need to direct politicians to.

The Banks! I hear tremendous talk about what can corporations do, what employers are doing for their employees. What are the banks doing about the decades of inflation that has made them trillionares? They are not charging us rates we can afford they charge us to make profits greater than the previous year, no two ways about it.

If politicians would force banks to reduce profit margins, interest margins, mortgages rates should be 0.0008% what good is my house if I cannot live and work to pay my bills? The ground / country the house the bank is billing me for is essentially useless if I cannot use it to live on!! This idea has to get out there!!
I have no soap box to stand on.
Instead of telling me to die off, tell the banks to stop charging me a rate to live that I cannot afford!
